@page "/privacy"
<PageTitle>Privacy Policy — Yesamanna</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Yesamanna Privacy Policy: what we collect, how we use data, cookies, and your rights." />
</HeadContent>

<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p><em>Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")</em></p>

<p>
    Yesamanna, a California LLC (“Yesamanna”, “we”, “us”), is committed to protecting your privacy.
    This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have.
</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<ul class="bullets">
    <li><strong>Account data:</strong> name, email, organization, and settings you provide.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> app interactions, device/browser info, diagnostics, and crash logs.</li>
    <li><strong>Content you submit:</strong> inputs, files, and feedback you choose to provide.</li>
    <li><strong>Payment data:</strong> processed by our payment provider; we do not store full card details.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Information</h2>
<ul class="bullets">
    <li>Provide and improve our services and features</li>
    <li>Authenticate users and maintain security</li>
    <li>Communicate updates and respond to support requests</li>
    <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
</ul>

<h2>Cookies & Tracking</h2>
<p>
    We use essential cookies for authentication and security, and optional analytics cookies to understand product usage.
    You can control cookies in your browser settings. Analytics are only used in aggregate.
</p>

<h2>Data Sharing</h2>
<ul class="bullets">
    <li><strong>Vendors:</strong> Trusted processors (e.g., hosting, analytics, payments) under data protection agreements.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal:</strong> When required by law or to protect rights, safety, and integrity.</li>
    <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> In merger, acquisition, or reorganization events, consistent with this policy.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Retention</h2>
<p>
    We retain information for as long as needed to provide the service and meet legal obligations.
    You may request deletion as described below.
</p>

<h2>Your Rights</h2>
<p>
    Depending on your region, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or export your data,
    and to object or restrict certain processing.
</p>

<h3>CCPA (California)</h3>
<ul class="bullets">
    <li>Right to know, delete, and non-discrimination for exercising rights</li>
    <li>We do not “sell” personal information as defined by CCPA</li>
</ul>

<h3>GDPR (EEA/UK)</h3>
<ul class="bullets">
    <li>Legal bases include contract, legitimate interests, consent, and legal obligations</li>
    <li>You may lodge a complaint with your local supervisory authority</li>
</ul>

<h2>Security</h2>
<p>
    We employ technical and organizational measures appropriate to risk, including encryption in transit,
    access controls, and regular monitoring. No method is 100% secure; please use strong, unique passwords.
</p>

<h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>
<p>
    Our services are not directed to children under 13 (or applicable age of digital consent).
    We do not knowingly collect data from children.
</p>

<h2>International Transfers</h2>
<p>
    Data may be processed in the United States and other countries. Where required, we use appropriate safeguards
    (e.g., SCCs) for international transfers.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>Questions or requests? Email <a href="mailto:info@yesamanna.com">info@yesamanna.com</a>.</p>

<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We’ll update this page when our practices change. Material changes will be notified through the app or email.</p>
